# AI-tool-specific outputs are generated from .rulesync/ via `rulesync generate`.
# Source of truth lives in .rulesync/. All AI-tool outputs (root-level CLAUDE.md
# and AGENTS.md included) are generated by `rulesync generate` and gitignored;
# the canonical content lives in .rulesync/rules/CLAUDE.md. Run
# `rulesync generate -t '*' -f '*'` after cloning to populate locally.
.memsearch/
# Claude Code + generic agent files
.claude/
.mcp.json
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
# Per-tool outputs from `rulesync generate -t '*'`. Each block is one tool;
# the .github/* entries are scoped on purpose — never blanket-ignore .github/,
# which holds tracked workflows, CODEOWNERS, dependabot, and templates.
.agent/
.agents/
.augment/
.cline/
.clinerules
.codex/
.copilot/
.cursor/
.cursorrules
.deepagents/
.factory/
.gemini/
